Q:  Describe the flow of how the Docker Client, Docker Daemon, and Docker Registry interact when you run docker run nginx.

Ans: 
Docker Client: Docker Client is like front desk that talks to Daemon and passes the command to it.

Docker Daemon: Docker Daemon received the request from the client and it checks whether the requested image is present in the system or not. 
If yes It uses the existing image to create and run the container
If not then it talks to the Docker registry and fetches the requested image to create and run the container

Docker Registry: It the place whether the downloaded are stored.
It receives the request from the Daemon and It pulls the requested image from registry.
The downloaded image stores in the system to create and run the container.



